China’s Pledge to Buy Hungarian Debt Is Unconditional, Napi Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-09-15T06:41:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/china-s-pledge-to-buy-hungarian-debt-is-unconditional-napi-says.html
China ’s pledge to buy foreign-
currency bonds issued by Hungary doesn’t carry special
conditions, Napi Gazdasag  reported , citing Debt Management
Agency Deputy Chief Executive Officer Laszlo Andras Borbely.  China’s offer may also include providing loans, Borbely
said, according to the business daily. Negotiations with China
are ongoing, Napi said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
